# Project Reference

## Tech Stack

- **Next.js 16** - App Router, Server Components, Server Actions
- **TypeScript** - Full type safety
- **Prisma** - ORM with SQLite/Turso/PostgreSQL
- **Auth.js v5** - Authentication (NextAuth)
- **Tailwind CSS** - Styling
- **shadcn/ui** - Component library
- **ULID** - Sortable unique IDs

## Project Structure

```
app/
├── actions/        # Server Actions
├── admin/          # Admin dashboard (protected)
├── api/            # API routes
├── auth/           # Auth pages
└── page.tsx        # Home

components/
├── ui/             # shadcn/ui components
├── auth/           # Auth forms
└── admin/          # Admin components

lib/
├── auth.ts         # Auth.js config
├── auth/           # Auth utilities
│   └── permissions.ts  # Role checking
├── prisma.ts       # Prisma client
└── logger.ts       # Logging

prisma/
├── schema.prisma   # Database schema
└── seed.ts         # Seed data

themes/             # Theme definitions
```

## Key Imports

```typescript
// Auth
import { auth } from "@/lib/auth"
import { getCurrentUser, isAdmin, hasRole } from "@/lib/auth/permissions"

// Database
import { prisma } from "@/lib/prisma"

// Logging (NEVER use console.log)
import { logger } from "@/lib/logger"
```

## Logging

**Always use logger, never console.log:**

```typescript
import { logger } from "@/lib/logger"

logger.info("User created", { userId: user.id })
logger.error("Failed to save", { error })
logger.warn("Deprecated endpoint")
logger.debug("Processing", { data })
```

## Database Models

- **User** - Accounts with email/password
- **UserProfile** - Extended user info
- **Role** - System roles (user, admin, custom)
- **UserRole** - Many-to-many user↔role

## ID Format

All IDs are ULID strings: `01JZK5AT1CBD1SBW5T3JQ60VPR`
- Auto-generated by Prisma middleware
- Sortable by creation time
- No `parseInt()` needed

## Common Commands

```bash
npm run setup          # Full setup
npm run dev            # Start dev server (use this, not dev:open)
npm run build          # Production build
npm run lint           # Lint code
npm run db:reset       # Reset database
npm run db:studio      # Database GUI
npx prisma migrate dev # Schema migration
```

## Starting the Dev Server

**IMPORTANT: Always run the dev server in the background.**

When the user asks to "run the server", "start the dev server", "npm run dev", or similar:
- Run `npm run dev` as a **background process** (not blocking)
- This allows you to continue helping while the server runs
- Watch output for: `Local: http://localhost:XXXX`

**After setup completes, you MUST:**

1. Run `npm run dev` (in background)
2. Watch output for: `Local: http://localhost:XXXX`
3. Open that URL in the browser

This ensures full log visibility and clean process management for restarts.

## Development Workflow

**After making code changes, verify before moving on:**

```bash
npx tsc --noEmit          # Quick type check (fastest)
npm run lint              # Check for issues
npm run build             # Full verification (before commit)
```

Run `npx tsc --noEmit` after every few edits to catch errors early.
Don't wait until commit time to discover type errors.

## Data Mutations

After any create/update/delete operation, always revalidate:

```typescript
import { revalidatePath } from "next/cache"

// After mutation
revalidatePath("/path/to/list")  // Or the list won't update
```

See SERVER-ACTIONS.mdc for full patterns.

## Common Runtime Errors

**Select components:** Never use `value=""` - causes crash
```typescript
// ❌ <SelectItem value="">None</SelectItem>
// ✅ <SelectItem value="none">None</SelectItem>
```

**After schema changes:** MUST restart dev server
```bash
npx prisma migrate dev --name "change"
npx prisma generate
# REQUIRED: Ctrl+C then npm run dev
```
Error if skipped: `Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'findMany')`

**Prisma dates in Server Actions:** Dates become strings after serialization
```typescript
// Server returns Date, client receives string
new Date(user.created_at).toLocaleDateString()  // ✅ Parse string to Date
user.created_at.toLocaleDateString()             // ❌ Fails - it's a string
```

See UI-COMPONENTS.mdc, DATABASE.mdc, and SERVER-ACTIONS.mdc for full patterns.

## Environment Variables

Required:
- `AUTH_SECRET` - Auth secret (64 hex chars)
- `NEXTAUTH_SECRET` - Must match AUTH_SECRET
- `DATABASE_URL` - Database connection
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` - Public URL

Optional:
- `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID/SECRET` - Google OAuth
- `GITHUB_CLIENT_ID/SECRET` - GitHub OAuth
- Storage provider credentials

## Security Checklist

- [ ] Auth checks on all protected routes
- [ ] Admin role verification
- [ ] Self-protection (can't remove own admin)
- [ ] Soft deletes (`deleted_at: null` filter)
- [ ] `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` on dynamic pages
- [ ] Never log sensitive data

## Multi-Page Navigation

**When adding multiple pages to the app, include a left sidebar for navigation:**

```tsx
// Layout with sidebar pattern
export default function Layout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <div className="flex min-h-screen">
      <aside className="w-64 border-r bg-muted/40">
        <nav className="flex flex-col gap-2 p-4">
          <Link href="/page1">Page 1</Link>
          <Link href="/page2">Page 2</Link>
        </nav>
      </aside>
      <main className="flex-1 p-6">{children}</main>
    </div>
  )
}
```

Use this pattern for any section with 2+ related pages.
